ANTHRAX - ARGENTINA (07): (BUENOS AIRES), BOVINE
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 15 Sep 2014
From: Ramon Noseda <rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar> [edited]


A cattle estancia in the county of Tapalque in Buenos Aires Province and close to the Altona railway station and along the Tapalque arroyo is presently flooded [thanks to some intense rainfall]. Since Thu 11 Sep 2014, they have had 14 breeding cows die out of 198 head. There were blood extravasations from the affected animals.

According to the ranch veterinarian, they have never had anthrax on this ranch before. The herd had not been vaccinated, though all the expected risk factors exist, fluctuating temperatures, heavy rain, alkaline soil, and high density grazing. According to the register of the Area de Evaluacion de Carbunclo Rural, the last outbreaks of anthrax in Tapalque county were in 2005 and 2006.

--
Ramon Noseda
CFO-Director/Microbiologist
Laboratorio Azul Diagnostico S.A.
Av. 25 de Mayo 479
(B 7300 FXE) Azul Bs. As.
Argentina
<rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar>

[For a map of Argentina showing the provinces, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_pol96.jpg. For Altona, southwest of Tapalque, go to: http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/01/Altona.html. To see what it looks like in that part of Argentina, go to: http://www.conocelaprovincia.com.ar/buenos_aires/altona.htm.

It is always difficult to come up with an explanation for such outbreaks on virgin establishments. The easiest explanation is that there were outbreaks before with previous owners but the information was not passed on. There are accounts of seasonal flooding transferring contaminated soil from one farm to another's "water meadows," pastures seasonally flooded, all easier to recount than to prove. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2775755,4.]
